"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/688080","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-02-20","<p>The Stakeholder Working Group on EU Exit, Universities, Research and Innovation had its first meeting on 14 December 2016. Membership of the Group includes representatives from Higher Education, Research and Innovation funders, National Academies, Learned Societies and Business. The full membership and the terms of reference will be published on Gov.uk shortly.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/688080/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T14:23:42.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/688080/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/688080/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-02-09","EU Exit, Universities, Research and Innovation Stakeholder Working Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the names are of the members of the High Level Stakeholder Working Group on EU Exit, Universities, Research and Innovation; how regularly that group meets; and what that group's terms of reference are.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","63880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/688081","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-03-08","<p>Ministers regularly meet new nuclear developers and the wider nuclear industry; this includes recent meetings with Toshiba and Nugen, with whom the Government remains in close contact as they develop their commercial plans.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/688081/answer",,,,,"63808","2017-03-08T16:15:28.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/688081/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/688081/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-02-09","Nuclear Power Stations: Cumbria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent representations he has received from Toshiba on the future of the planned nuclear plant at Moorside; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","63809"
