"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686949","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-24","<p>The estimated cost to the Exchequer from employer pension contributions not being subject to employee and employer National Insurance is included in HM Revenue and Customs’ (HMRC’s) National Statistics publication, and is available to view here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/registered-pension-schemes-cost-of-tax-relief" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/registered-pension-schemes-cost-of-tax-relief</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The requested information is not reported to HMRC.</p><p> </p><p>Information on private pension membership is published by the Office for National Statistics here: <a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/personalandhouseholdfinances/pensionssavingsandinvestments" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/personalandhouseholdfinances/pensionssavingsandinvestments</a>.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686949/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T12:35:38.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686949/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686949/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-02-08","Pensions: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many (a) people and (b) businesses received national insurance contributions relief for employer contributions to registered pensions schemes in (i) 2013-14 and (ii) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","63619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686950","HM Treasury","false","2017-02-24","<p>It is estimated that, during 2013-14, an average of 680,000 employees received National Insurance relief for the three forms of employer-supported childcare. The corresponding estimate for 2014-15 is 740,000.</p><p> </p><p>Estimates for the corresponding number of businesses are not available.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686950/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T12:19:35.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686950/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/686950/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-02-08","Day Care: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many (a) people and (b) businesses received national insurance contributions relief for employer supported childcare including workplace nurseries in (i) 2013-14 and (ii) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","63620"
