"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687014","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>Our Consulate General in Jerusalem frequently raises this issue with the Palestinian Water Authority, a body of the Palestinian Authority. We have serious concerns about the quality of water in Gaza, and note that the World Health Organisation has assessed that 90-95% of water in Gaza is undrinkable. UK technical assistance has aided the feasibility study of a proposed Gaza desalinisation plant.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687014/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T16:18:47.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687014/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687014/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Gaza: Water","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Palestinian authorities on water quality in Gaza.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","63583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687015","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>While we have not raised this specific issue, we have consistently called on the Israeli Government to ease movement and access restrictions in the Occupied Palestinian Territories. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv most recently did so on 19 January.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687015/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T16:21:59.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687015/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687015/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Gaza: Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Israeli authorities on the quality of people's health in Gaza.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","63584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687016","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>​It is difficult to hold any discussions on tax avoidance and evasion with the Pitcairn Islands as they do not have a financial centre.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687016/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T14:10:28.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687016/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687016/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Pitcairn Islands: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has discussed tax (a) avoidance and (b) evasion with the Government of the Pitcairn Islands since the last Joint Ministerial Council.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","63562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687017","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>It is difficult to hold any discussions on tax avoidance and evasion with Tristan da Cunha as they do not have a financial centre.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687017/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T14:41:31.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687017/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687017/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Tristan da Cunha: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has discussed tax (a) avoidance and (b) evasion with the Government of Tristan da Cunha since the last Joint Ministerial Council.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","63563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687018","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>It is difficult to hold any discussions on tax avoidance and evasion with St Helena as they do not have a financial centre.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687018/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T14:06:33.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687018/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687018/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","St Helena: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has discussed tax (a) avoidance and (b) evasion with the Government of St Helena since the last Joint Ministerial Council.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","63560"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687019","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>We have a strong and growing bilateral relationship with the Philippines, which covers a range of issues including peace and security, counter terrorism, counter extremism, and human rights. We remain actively involved in efforts to promote stability, particularly in the southern Philippines. During my visit to Manila last December, I met senior members of the Philippine Administration and discussed how we can strengthen our cooperation. We will continue to offer support, drawing in particular on UK expertise in these areas.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687019/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T13:08:09.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687019/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687019/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Philippines: Emergency Powers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to promote stability and support the Philippines during its state of national emergency.","false","Biography information for Claire Perry","Devizes","Claire Perry","63561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687020","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>As the Minister for Immigration at the Home Office, my Hon. Friend the Member for Scarborough and Whitby (Mr Goodwill) said in his written response to you on 30 January [61657], the primary responsibility for refugees outside the UK rests with the host country within which they are residing. I am the Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) Minister of State with responsibility for Europe. The migration crisis is regularly raised in European discussions, such as the European Council attended by the Prime Minister, and Foreign Affairs Council, attended by the Foreign Secretary.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687020/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T13:51:40.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687020/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687020/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Syria: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, which Minister in his Department leads on discussions at EU level on the wellbeing of Syrian refugees who have entered mainland Europe.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","63772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687021","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to my answer of 9 June 2016 (PQ 39140). Shortly after the visit of the former Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), Zainab Al Khawaja was released from prison on 31 May 2016. We raised Zainab Al Khawaja’s case regularly at a senior level with the Government of Bahrain prior to her release from prison on 31 May 2016.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687021/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T16:47:21.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687021/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687021/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Zainab al-Khawaja","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the Bahrainian Government on the case of Zainab Al-Khawaja.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","63677"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687022","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>The British Government has made clear publicly the importance of all parties adhering to the ceasefire deal in Syria. We discuss the situation in Syria regularly with Turkey and Russia. Within international fora such as the UN Security Council and the International Syria Support Group (ISSG), we have highlighted the importance of strengthening and building confidence in the ceasefire; we did this most recently on 2 February.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687022/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T16:42:13.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687022/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687022/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to work with the Governments of Turkey and Russia on maximising the likelihood of adherence to the ceasefire in Syria.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","63717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687023","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>The UK continues to support all efforts to strengthen the ceasefire in Syria, enable humanitarian access and support a return to negotiations on a political settlement. Russia, Turkey and Iran - the guarantors of the 30 December ceasefire agreement – have proposed a trilateral mechanism to monitor the ceasefire. To be effective, such a mechanism will need to be genuinely independent and closely coordinated with the United Nations. The UK will continue to speak out, including at the regular meetings of the International Syria Support Group Ceasefire Task Force, should these basic elements of a ceasefire not be adhered to.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687023/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T16:45:09.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687023/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687023/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to monitor adherence to the ceasefire in Syria.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","63718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687024","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>Following the signing of the Executive Order on 27 January, the Foreign Secretary engaged senior contacts in the US Administration, and the Home Secretary spoke with her US counterpart, in order to clarify that all British passport holders remain welcome to travel to the United States, and the Executive Order will make no difference to any British passport-holder, irrespective of their country of birth or whether they hold another passport.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687024/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T13:55:11.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687024/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687024/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","USA: Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he plans to make representations to the US Administration on the recent changes in US immigration policy.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","63692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687025","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>The Office of the Public Prosecution announced on 23 November 2016 that the case against Ebrahim Sharif had been closed and the charges against him dropped. We welcome the positive outcome on this case.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687025/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T16:32:33.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687025/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687025/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Ibrahim Sharif","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the Bahrainian Government on the case of Ebrahim Sharif.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","63682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687026","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office issued a statement at the time, expressing concern at the revocation of Sheikh Isa Qassim’s nationality. We have also raised this at Ministerial level. Sheikh Isa is currently the subject of a separate, ongoing court case. Embassy officials have attended every hearing in this trial to date and we will continue to monitor the case closely.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687026/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T16:36:07.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687026/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687026/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Sheikh Isa Qassim","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the Bahrainian Government on the case of Sheikh Isa Qassim.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","63683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687027","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>The UK Government has continued to emphasise to the Bahraini Government the need to respect the rights of all citizens and to act proportionately to protect human rights, including freedom of expression.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687027/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T16:38:06.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687027/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687027/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Bahrain: Journalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the Bahrainian Government on licence renewals for journalists.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","63684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687028","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Mr Johnson), issued a statement expressing concerns on the day of the Bahraini High Administrative Court’s decision to dissolve the main Bahraini Shia opposition political society Al Wefaq. <br> <br>We have raised our concerns about the case of Sheikh Ali Salman at Ministerial level, including during the visit of the former Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), to Bahrain in May 2016. Embassy officials have attended every hearing and we continue to monitor the case closely.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687028/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T16:30:59.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687028/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687028/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Bahrain: Al Wefaq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the Bahrainian Government on the (a) dissolution of the Al-Wefaq political party and (b) imprisonment of Sheikh Ali Salman.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","63681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687029","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>As Mr Halawa is an Irish citizen, the Irish Government is taking the lead on his case and has been monitoring his trial; we have offered our support. FCO Ministers have asked the Egyptian authorities to review mass judicial decisions and we continue to raise concerns regarding reports of torture and mistreatment in detention with the Egyptian authorities. We have also raised our concerns at the UN, most recently at the Human Rights Council in September. In our statement we raised our concerns about reports of torture, poor detention conditions and the handing down of death sentences, as well as mass trials.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687029/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T13:18:31.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687029/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687029/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Ibrahim Halawa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the Egyptian authorities on the case of Ibrahim Halawa.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","63685"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687030","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>The Government has regular discussions, including at Ministerial level, on the issue of the operation of civil societies in Bahrain. We continue to encourage Bahrain to develop an enabling atmosphere for participation in society of all its citizens. We are assisting the Ministry of Labour and Social Development and the civil society sector more broadly to help to create a more enabling environment for Non-Government Organisations and civil society.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687030/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T16:28:04.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687030/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687030/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Bahrain: Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of reports that Bahrain's anti-terrorism legislation has been used to target civil society organisations and human rights activists in that country.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","63680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687031","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>​We have raised the allegations of travel bans at senior levels within the Government of Bahrain, particularly with regard to reports of Human Rights Defenders being prevented from travelling to the Human Rights Council in Geneva last year. We will continue to raise concerns where we have them.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687031/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T16:23:39.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687031/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687031/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Bahrain: Travel Restrictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the Bahrainian Government on the imposition of travel bans on human rights defenders, trade unionists, lawyers and political activists.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","63678"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687032","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>The Government has regular discussions, including at Ministerial level, on the issue of the operation of civil societies in Bahrain. We continue to encourage Bahrain to develop an enabling atmosphere for participation in society by all of its citizens. We are assisting the Ministry of Labour and Social Development and the civil society sector more broadly to help to create a more enabling environment for Non-Government Organisations and civil society.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687032/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T16:25:58.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687032/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687032/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Bahrain: Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the Bahrainian Government on the operation of civil societies.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","63679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687033","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","true","2017-02-24","<p>​</p><p><del class="ministerial">The Ukrainian authorities estimate that there are up to 3500 Russian nationals fighting in eastern Ukraine. We are also aware of reports of a relatively small number of other nationals present in eastern Ukraine. The presence of Russian fighters in Ukraine remains a key obstacle to progress in implementing the Minsk peace agreement, which requires the withdrawal of all foreign armed formations, military equipment and mercenaries from the territory of Ukraine.</del><ins class="ministerial">Given that these territories are not under Government control, there are clear logistical limitations to service provision by the Ukrainian Government to civilians living there. Nonetheless, the Ukrainian Government continues to provide water, heating and energy supplies to non-Government held areas. The UK provides close support to the Ministry for Temporarily Occupied Territories and Internally Displaced Persons and we welcome the Ukrainian Government’s efforts to pursue further ways to provide support to those in non-Government controlled areas, including by facilitating crossings and the transport of goods across the Line of Contact. However, the best way to secure the provision of services to civilians across the Donbas would be a full and comprehensive ceasefire; ongoing fighting poses a grave threat to vital utilities as well as civilian lives, as seen recently in Avdiivka.</ins></p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687033/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T09:53:29.997Z","2017-02-27T10:59:41.447Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687033/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687033/answer","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687033/answer/previousversion/36743","Biography information for Boris Johnson","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Ukraine: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the capacity of the Ukrainian authorities to provide government services to civilians living in districts under separatist control; and what representations he has made to his Ukrainian counterpart on the provision of services to such civilians.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","63634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687034","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>The conflict in eastern Ukraine continues to have a devastating effect on millions of civilians living on both sides of the Line of Contact. Reports by the Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe (OSCE) that all sides have used civilian areas for military purposes are very concerning. We welcome recent efforts by the Ukrainian Government to repair civilian infrastructure in Avdiivka damaged by fighting, and condemn the fact that civilian repair teams came under fire while carrying out this vital work. We regularly raise these issues with the Governments of both Russia and Ukraine, emphasising the need for all sides to abide by the Minsk agreements, which call for heavy weaponry to be withdrawn from the Line of Contact. But we are clear that the fundamental cause of this conflict remains Russia’s continuing attempts to destabilise Ukraine through its support for separatist forces, including through the provision of military equipment and troops.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687034/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T12:53:08.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687034/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687034/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Ukraine: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the Government of (a) Ukraine and (b) Russia on the presence of military equipment and troops in civilian-populated areas of eastern Ukraine.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","63635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687035","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>The Ukrainian authorities estimate that there are up to 3500 Russian nationals fighting in eastern Ukraine. We are also aware of reports of a relatively small number of other nationals present in eastern Ukraine. The presence of Russian fighters in Ukraine remains a key obstacle to progress in implementing the Minsk peace agreement, which requires the withdrawal of all foreign armed formations, military equipment and mercenaries from the territory of Ukraine.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687035/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T09:54:09.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687035/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687035/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Ukraine: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent estimate he has made of the number of foreign fighters in eastern Ukraine.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","63636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687036","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-02-24","<p>The UN estimate that up to 0.8 million people reside in areas near the line of contact which have the potential to be affected by fighting, and that 2.3 million people are resident in areas under the control of Russian-backed separatists.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687036/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T13:00:07.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687036/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687036/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-02-08","Ukraine: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent estimate he has made of the number of Ukrainian civilians living along the line of separation between the breakaway districts of the Donetsk and Luhansk oblasts and the rest of Ukraine; and the number of civilians living in combat zones on either side of that line.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","63637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687037","Department of Health","false","2017-02-24","<p>The Department is developing plans to establish a new National Health Service property organisation, in response to early recommendations made by Sir Robert Naylor’s ongoing review of the NHS estate. A key function of the new organisation will be to provide a single strengthened source of strategic estates planning expertise for the NHS. This will build on the support that existing teams in NHS Property Services and Community Health Partnerships have been providing to the NHS locally, including in the development of estates proposals as part of sustainability and transformation plans.</p><p> </p><p>Further details on the proposed new organisation, including its organisational form, will be set out in due course. We are committed to ensuring that the new organisation fully supports and reflects the needs and priorities of the NHS.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687037/answer",,,,,"63652","2017-02-24T10:29:10.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687037/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687037/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","NHS Property Services and Community Health Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what proposals he has received on the organisational form of the new body to be created from the merger of NHS Property Services and Community Health Partnerships; and what role sustainability and transformation plans will play in determining that organisational form.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","63649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687038","Department of Health","false","2017-02-22","<p>NHS England is responsible for commissioning specialised neurological services, including some services for patients with neuromuscular disorders. NHS England has published a service specification for neurological care that includes an exemplar service specification for neuromuscular conditions that sets out what providers must have in place to offer evidence-based, safe and effective services. The service specification for neurological care can be found at the following link:</p><p><a href="http://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/d04-neurosci-spec-neuro.pdf" target="_blank">www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/d04-neurosci-spec-neuro.pdf</a></p><p>The responsibility for delivering the service rests with National Health Service provider organisations, and each trust will develop an appropriate role to ensure that the care pathway is delivered. The role may vary depending on the provider organisation, but an NHS England service specialist will be working with trusts to ensure that they meet the requirements of the overall service specification.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687038/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-22T09:58:10.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687038/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687038/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Neuromuscular Disorders: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 25 January 2017 to Question 60683, on neuromuscular disorders: South East, how many neuromuscular care advisors will cover Kent, Surrey and Sussex; which clinical commissioning groups in Kent, Surrey and Sussex will contribute to funding neuromuscular care advisor roles; what the remit will be of Brighton and Sussex University Hospitals NHS Trust in this process; and when it is planned for relevant clinical commissioning groups to finalise job descriptions and begin recruitment.","false","Biography information for Caroline Ansell","Eastbourne","Caroline Ansell","63661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687039","Department of Health","false","2017-02-20","<p>The Government set a national ambition in April 2016 to eliminate inappropriate out of area placements (OAPs) for adult acute inpatient care by 2020/21.</p><p> </p><p>A bespoke data collection has been commissioned to capture details of OAPs in mental health services, and has been reporting data since December 2016. This collection was introduced in order to establish a reliable national baseline of OAPs, and understand where and why OAPs are happening. The collection will support the development of a clear national trajectory for reducing OAPs over the next four years, in order to achieve the ambition by 2020/21. NHS England and its arm’s length bodies are aligning levers and incentives across the system to ensure that the elimination of OAPs is reflected as a clear system-wide priority.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England plans to publish an evidence based treatment pathway for acute mental health care by the end of 2016/17, including clear response times, quality guidelines and benchmarks. The accompanying implementation guidance will support local service capacity assessment and improvement programmes. It will advocate whole-system and partnership working across housing, social care, and the voluntary sector. NHS England is investing more than £400 million over four years from 2017/18 in crisis resolution and home treatment teams to provide an alternative to admission when it is safe to do so, reducing pressure on inpatient capacity and supporting more people to access care locally and in a timely manner.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687039/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T11:59:29.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687039/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687039/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Mental Health Services: Out of Area Treatment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps the Government is taking to phase out the practice of out-of-area placements across England, as recommended by the Commission on Acute Adult Psychiatric Care.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","63648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687040","Department of Health","false","2017-02-22","<p>In line with the General Practice Forward View, NHS England will be providing £326,000 of “resilience funding” to help general practitioner (GP) practices in Bristol, North Somerset and South Gloucestershire tackle rising pressure and workload.</p><p> </p><p>This funding is being delegated to Bristol, North Somerset and South Gloucestershire (BNSSG) Clinical Commissioning Groups (CCGs) which have added an additional £200,000 of funding to enable the 18 clusters of GP practices to work together to develop a resilience plan tailored to the local area. The funding is being used for a BNSSG wide initiative which includes reducing use of locum staff, establishing flexible working and running a joint recruitment campaign.</p><p> </p><p>Practices facing particular challenges will also be offered close support from neighbouring practice managers and clinical staff. The funding allocation was agreed by NHS England South (South West) Directors in August last year and notified to all local GP practices by CCGs and Sustainability and Transformation Plan leaders. NHS England is currently transferring the funding to the CCGs under a Memorandum of Understanding.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687040/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-22T10:03:06.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687040/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687040/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","General Practitioners: South West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he plans for NHS England to publish its plans for allocation of the £326,000 of funding from the General Practice Forward View to be spent in the Bristol, North Somerset and South Gloucestershire Sustainability and Transformation Plan.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","63651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687041","Department of Health","false","2017-02-24","<p>NHS Protect's investigation into this matter is ongoing and it is not possible to provide a timescale for its conclusion whilst lines of enquiry continue to be pursued.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687041/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T10:23:49.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687041/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687041/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Phil Morley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the timescale is for NHS Protect's investigation into the conduct of Phil Morley while he was Chief Executive of the Hull and East Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","63667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687042","Department of Health","false","2017-02-20","<p>No discussions have been held with the Welsh Assembly Government on this matter. A letter has been received recently from the Welsh Cabinet Secretary for Health, Well-being and Sport.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687042/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T11:50:33.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687042/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687042/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent discussions he has had with the Welsh Assembly Government on holding a public inquiry into the contaminated blood scandal.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","63668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687043","Department of Health","false","2017-02-20","<p>In order for NHS England to formally consider a new or revised service specification, a number of associated reports and processes need to be completed. The Complex Gynaecological Services Clinical Reference Group (CRG) did start the process of developing a new service specification for ovarian cancer, however, it did not complete the process. The CRG encountered technical difficulties during the Impact Assessment stage including issues identifying activity and the associated financial impact.</p><p> </p><p>In the subsequent period, CRGs have been restructured and the responsibility for this clinical area now resides with the Specialised Cancer Surgery CRG, within the National Cancer Programme of Care. In addition, NHS England has also published a revised process for service specification development (titled: ‘Methods’), which can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/spec-services/key-docs/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/spec-services/key-docs/</a></p><p> </p><p>The Methods sets out the process for completing service specification work and, in accordance with this process, the Specialised Cancer Surgery CRG has been asked to consider progressing this work. It is expected that the first step of the process will be completed by the end of February 2017.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687043/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T15:40:53.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687043/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687043/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Ovarian Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when he plans to publish the ovarian cancer-specific service specification submitted for approval by the Complex Gynaecological Services Clinical Reference Group in 2015.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","63653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687044","Department of Health","false","2017-02-24","<p>The Department has provided an additional £127 million to the NHS England Mandate to fund the increased costs within the National Health Service of this policy change. Where the occupier delivers services that are commissioned by a clinical commissioning group or NHS England they are expected to be reimbursed the impact of the application of the market rents policy with effect from 2016/17 financial year by the relevant commissioning body.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687044/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-24T10:22:08.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687044/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687044/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Clinical Commissioning Groups: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has to continue to provide additional funding to cover increases in market rents in buildings from which clinical commissioning groups commission services.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","63650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687045","Department of Health","false","2017-02-24","<p>The Department is developing plans to establish a new National Health Service property organisation, in response to early recommendations made by Sir Robert Naylor’s ongoing review of the NHS estate. A key function of the new organisation will be to provide a single strengthened source of strategic estates planning expertise for the NHS. This will build on the support that existing teams in NHS Property Services and Community Health Partnerships have been providing to the NHS locally, including in the development of estates proposals as part of sustainability and transformation plans.</p><p> </p><p>Further details on the proposed new organisation, including its organisational form, will be set out in due course. We are committed to ensuring that the new organisation fully supports and reflects the needs and priorities of the NHS.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687045/answer",,,,,"63649","2017-02-24T10:29:11.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687045/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687045/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","NHS Property Services and Community Health Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will publish the business case for the creation of a new organisation from NHS Property Services and Community Health Partnerships.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","63652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687046","Department of Health","false","2017-02-20","<p>The Department has made no such estimate. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) is currently appraising brentuximab for treating CD30+ Hodgkin lymphoma and recently consulted on its draft guidance. NICE has not yet published final guidance. Brentuximab is currently available to National Health Service patients with relapsed and refractory Hodgkin lymphoma through the Cancer Drugs Fund.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687046/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T09:58:34.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687046/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687046/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Brentuximab Vedotin","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of how many relapsed/refractory Hodgkin lymphoma patients will not receive stem cell transplants if brentuximab vedotin is removed as a standard of care.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","63694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687047","Department of Health","false","2017-02-20","<p>Public Health England (PHE) published it’s alcohol evidence review, in December 2016, which included data on alcohol related hospital admissions.</p><p> </p><p>There are a range of actions underway to tackle alcohol harm, and which are aimed to prevent alcohol-related hospital admissions. These include:</p><p>- a new national programme to incentivise screening and provide appropriate interventions to all in patients in National Health Service hospitals is being rolled out over the next two years;</p><p>- many Sustainability and Transformation Plan footprint areas have used PHE’s menu of preventative interventions to guide their decisions on local action to reduce alcohol harm and hospital admissions; and</p><p>- more widely, PHE’s One You campaign includes tools to help those people who want to reduce their consumption of alcohol, and the NHS health check continues to promote interventions to reduce harm and offer alcohol treatment for people who need help to recover from dependence.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687047/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T12:04:45.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687047/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687047/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Alcoholic Drinks: Misuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of trends in hospital admissions due to alcohol in the last 10 years; and what steps his Department is taking to reduce such admissions.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","63710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687048","Department of Health","false","2017-02-20","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687048/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T14:29:40.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687048/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687048/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Health Professions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many registered health professionals were directly employed by his Department on 1 February (a) 2017 and (b) 2016; and how many such professionals in each of those years were in which profession.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","63716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687049","Department of Health","false","2017-02-22","<p>NHS England published its policy on Transcatheter Aortic Valve Implantation (TAVI) For Aortic Stenosis in 2013. The policy is available here:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/a09-p-a.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/a09-p-a.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The evidence base was reviewed again in 2015 but was not considered sufficiently strong to warrant changing the current policy. Clinical advice indicated that there was a need to consider the Aortic Stenosis pathway as a whole and the different surgical approaches, rather than only considering TAVI. Further work on this pathway is expected to take place in 2017/18 as part of the Internal Medicine Work Programme.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England’s policy position on Aortic Stenosis, including TAVI, is also expected to be within the scope of the national Cardiac Review, which will begin in 2017. Stakeholder engagement is informing the scope of the review and further public engagement will be integral to informing NHS England’s future commissioning approach.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has not set a cap on the number of TAVI procedures at a national or local level, where the published policy states that TAVI would be routinely commissioned.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687049/answer",,,,,"63750 ; 63752","2017-02-22T10:00:46.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687049/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687049/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Heart Diseases: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the Internal Medicine commissioning policy plans are for the provision of Transcatheter Aortic Valve Implantation; and if he will ensure that such plans are published.","false","Biography information for Derek Thomas","St Ives","Derek Thomas","63751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687050","Department of Health","false","2017-02-20","<p>NHS Digital publishes data on the nationality of staff working in the National Health Service in England. Nationality is self-reported within the NHS human resources and payroll system, the electronic staff record.</p><p>In October 2016, 977 (2.5%) psychiatric nurses working in NHS trusts and clinical commissioning groups declared their nationality as other European Union nationals, excluding the United Kingdom. This is out of a total headcount of 38,332.</p><p>The October data is the most recent data available.</p><p>The potential effect on nationals and productivity of leaving the EU will be dependent on the outcome of negotiations. The Prime Minister has been clear that she wants to protect the status of EU nationals already living here. It is the Government’s aim to get the best settlement for the UK in all areas including the healthcare system.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687050/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T10:22:00.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687050/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687050/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Psychiatric Nurses: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of nationals of other EU countries currently working in the NHS as psychiatric nurses; what the potential effect of the UK leaving the EU would be on the number of such nurses; and what the potential effect on NHS productivity of that change in the number of such nurses would be.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","63731"
