"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687072","Department of Health","false","2017-02-20","<p>The Department allocated funding of over £8 billion to local authorities from 2013/14 to 2015/16. It is not possible to provide a break-down of the estimated spend by local authorities and clinical commissioning groups on early years support for children and families for the last year in each region of England.</p><p>2015-16 data for individual local authorities can be viewed on the National Statistics website at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing-england-2015-to-2016-individual-local-authority-data-outturn" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing-england-2015-to-2016-individual-local-authority-data-outturn</a></p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687072/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T11:53:49.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687072/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687072/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Health: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will estimate the amount of funding spent by (a) clinical commissioning groups and (b) local authorities on supporting children and families in the early years in (i) England, (ii) each region and (iii) each local authority.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","63571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687073","Department of Health","false","2017-02-20","<p>The information is not collected in the requested format.</p><p> </p><p>It is important to note that perinatal mental illness includes a range of conditions, including antenatal depression, postnatal depression, maternal obsessive compulsive disorder, post-traumatic stress disorder and postpartum psychosis.</p><p>NHS Digital has started to publish monthly experimental statistics collected via the Mental Health Dataset (MHDS) which include basic caseload measures for community based specialist perinatal mental health services.</p><p>NHS Digital is working with system partners to further develop perinatal mental health metrics for the MHDS collection.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687073/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T11:49:14.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687073/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687073/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-02-08","Pregnancy: Depressive Illnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many cases of perinatal depression there have been recorded in each (a) region and (b) clinical commissioning group area in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","63572"
