"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687081","Home Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>This issue was resolved on 19 April 2016.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687081/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T13:07:51.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687081/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687081/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-08","Police National Computer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 2 February 2017 to Question 61991, on what date the issue of the omission relating to the recording of licence conditions on the Police National Computer was resolved.","false","Biography information for Johnny Mercer","Plymouth, Moor View","Johnny Mercer","63593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687082","Home Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>The National DNA Database does not contain information on whether a profile is from a serving prisoner. However, there are good reasons to believe that a significant majority of the prison population has a profile on the NDNAD. Police forces have had the power to retain DNA taken from those convicted of recordable offences since the establishment of the DNA database in 1995 and legal powers have existed since 1996 to take DNA samples from those in prison.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687082/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T13:05:33.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687082/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687082/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-08","DNA: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of prisoners in England and Wales have a profile on the national DNA database.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","63609"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687083","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-02-20","<p>The data on the number of offenders with 15 or more previous cautions or convictions is available on <a href="http://www.gov.uk" target="_blank">GOV.</a>UK.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687083/answer",,,,,"63611","2017-02-20T18:00:08.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687083/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687083/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-02-08","Police Cautions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have been given 15 cautions or more in each of the last five years by age group.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","63610"
