"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687088","Home Office","false","2017-02-20","<p>We are reviewing the identification of and support provided to victims of modern slavery and are piloting a new National Referral Mechanism model. The pilot is due to end on 31 March and will be fully evaluated. The Independent Anti-Slavery Commissioner’s letter will be considered alongside the full evaluation of the pilot.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687088/answer",,,,,,"2017-02-20T12:56:18.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687088/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/687088/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-02-08","Slavery: Victim Support Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she plans to take in response to the letter of 10 January 2017 from the Independent Anti-Slavery Commissioner on identifying, referring and supporting victims of modern slavery in the UK's National Referral Mechanism.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","63608"
